<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-26T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/316: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Carter</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-26T12:00:00-05:00">February 26,
                                1930—noon</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>22. Your 28, February 22, 3 p.m. You may inform the Liberian Government
                            that the United States Government withdraws the nomination of Captain
                            Outley as made under the 1912 Loan Agreement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>